A man in his seventies died after his house in Serpentine Road in Westville, Durban, caught alight.
Rescue Care Spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said today that when paramedics arrived at about 2pm they found a severely burnt body. He said the cause of the fire was not yet established.
The South African Police Service and the Durban Fire Department are investigating.
– African News Agency (ANA)
